5	This chapter introduces the project's named declaration for the M2.a sub-step of the genus-$0$ Albanese-witness argument: rigidity of morphisms from a smooth proper geometrically irreducible curve of genus $0$ to a smooth proper geometrically irreducible group scheme, \textbf{over an algebraically closed base field $\bar k$ of characteristic zero} (the alg-closed pivot of \S "Iter-152 alg-closed pivot" below; descent of the constancy conclusion to a general base field $k$ is a separate downstream step, hosted in the genus-$0$ witness chapter). The classical statement (Mumford, \emph{Abelian Varieties}, Chapter~II~\S4) is
